2) **Chaotic lattice background** (subtle prism + grain, animated drift)

Do these exactly:

---

### 1) Bump the base font size
Open `src/app/layout.tsx` and tweak the `<body>` class:

```tsx
<body className="bg-[#0f1113] text-zinc-100 antialiased text-[17px] sm:text-[18px] leading-relaxed">
```

That lifts the whole site without messing spacing.

---

### 2) Add the chaotic background
**A.** In `src/app/layout.tsx`, add a fixed background layer right inside `<body>` (before `<header>`):

```tsx
<div
  aria-hidden
  className="pointer-events-none fixed inset-0 -z-10 ci-bg"
></div>
```

**B.** Open `src/app/globals.css` and append this at the bottom:

```css
/* ===== Chaotic Instinct Background ===== */
@keyframes ci-drift {
  0%   { transform: translateY(0px) rotate(0deg) scale(1); }
  50%  { transform: translateY(-8px) rotate(1deg) scale(1.02); }
  100% { transform: translateY(0px) rotate(0deg) scale(1); }
}

/* Subtle prism lattice + grain overlay */
.ci-bg {
  position: fixed;
  inset: 0;
  /* Layer 1: deep radial glow */
  background:
    radial-gradient(1200px 800px at 10% 0%, rgba(120,120,255,0.10), transparent 60%),
    radial-gradient(900px 600px at 90% 20%, rgba(255,120,200,0.08), transparent 60%),
    radial-gradient(700px 500px at 50% 100%, rgba(120,255,200,0.06), transparent 60%),
    /* Layer 2: faint conic prism rings */
    conic-gradient(from 220deg at 60% 40%,
      rgba(255,255,255,0.08),
      rgba(255,255,255,0.00) 25%,
      rgba(255,255,255,0.06) 50%,
      rgba(255,255,255,0.00) 75%,
      rgba(255,255,255,0.08) 100%),
    /* Layer 3: lattice lines */
    repeating-linear-gradient(
      125deg,
      rgba(255,255,255,0.06) 0px,
      rgba(255,255,255,0.06) 1px,
      transparent 1px,
      transparent 22px
    ),
    repeating-linear-gradient(
      55deg,
      rgba(255,255,255,0.04) 0px,
      rgba(255,255,255,0.04) 1px,
      transparent 1px,
      transparent 18px
    );
  mix-blend-mode: normal;
  filter: saturate(105%) contrast(105%);
  opacity: 0.55;
  animation: ci-drift 18s ease-in-out infinite;
}

/* Layer 4: super-faint grain (data-URI SVG) */
.ci-bg::after {
  content: "";
  position: absolute;
  inset: -10%;
  pointer-events: none;
  background-image: url("data:image/svg+xml;utf8,\
  <svg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' width='120' height='120' viewBox='0 0 120 120'>\
    <filter id='n'><feTurbulence type='fractalNoise' baseFrequency='0.9' numOctaves='2' stitchTiles='stitch'/></filter>\
    <rect width='120' height='120' filter='url(%23n)' opacity='0.06'/>\
  </svg>");
  background-size: 180px 180px;
  opacity: 0.7;
}
```

That gives you: dark base, spectral glows, faint intersecting lines, and a whisper of grain—**chaos, but disciplined**. It’s lightweight and A11y‑friendly.

---

