## How to plug this into your app
1) Drop these three files into your repo at `ui/static/`.
2) From your existing dashboard (or as a quick check), open `tornado.html` in a browser to verify visuals.
3) In your real dashboard page, include:
```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/ui/static/tornado.css" />
<script src="/ui/static/tornado.js" defer></script>
```
…and add the `#tm-container` block in the appropriate panel.

4) From your app logic, trigger:
```js
// start scan
window.TornadoMan.scanning();

// when a feature is locked by tier
window.TornadoMan.lockedFeature();

// when a feature doesn’t exist
window.TornadoMan.missingFeature();

// after completion
window.TornadoMan.scanDone();
```
…and set tier on login:
```js
window.TornadoManSet.setMode('subscription'); // or 'beta' | 'enterprise'
```

## Performance notes (no compromises)
- Filters are scoped to the SVG element; `action` adds blur only during spin.
- The swirl uses a handful of `<ellipse>` bands (cheap to render), displaced by noise for that “shader” feel without GPU drag.
- Tie is independent of swirl filter so its edges stay razor‑sharp (brand anchor).
- Dark/light themes work by only changing CSS variables.

If you want, I can also hand you a **Canvas/WebGL** variant for even higher throughput on monster scans, but this SVG stack will already feel smooth on mobile and desktop.

You get this integrated, and your UI won’t feel “placeholder”—it’ll feel alive, premium, and perfectly on‑brand.

